dc_description_s: 1 map ; 45 x 55 cm.|Relief shown pictorially.|Decorative title cartouche bordered by frame with branches at top and the coat of arms of the King of France and Navarre at bottom. The scale cartouche depicts dividers.|This state was published in Jan Jansson's Theatrum Universa Galliae between 1631 and 1633.|From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan.
